!=========================================================================
! NOTES FOR FWI POST-PROCESSING
!=========================================================================
! The Canadian Fire Weather Index (FWI) System requires:
!
! From WRF Output (wrfout_d0X_*):
!   - T2      : 2-meter temperature (K) -> convert to °C
!   - Q2      : 2-meter specific humidity (kg/kg) -> convert to RH%
!   - PSFC    : Surface pressure (Pa) - needed for RH calculation
!   - U10     : 10-meter U wind component (m/s)
!   - V10     : 10-meter V wind component (m/s) -> combine for wind speed
!   - RAINNC  : Non-convective precipitation (mm)
!   - RAINC   : Convective precipitation (mm) -> sum for total precip
!
! FWI Components calculated from above:
!   - FFMC : Fine Fuel Moisture Code (T, RH, Wind, Rain)
!   - DMC  : Duff Moisture Code (T, RH, Rain)
!   - DC   : Drought Code (T, Rain)
!   - ISI  : Initial Spread Index (FFMC, Wind)
!   - BUI  : Buildup Index (DMC, DC)
!   - FWI  : Fire Weather Index (ISI, BUI)
!
! Temporal Requirements:
!   - Noon local time values (12:00 LST) for standard FWI
!   - history_interval = 60 provides hourly data for flexibility
!=========================================================================
